===Noun===
'''Loch''' (pl. ''Löcher'')

# [[hole]]
# (dentistry) [[cavity]]
# (electronics) [[p-hole]]
# (coll.) a room, apartment, flat or house in a bad condition; [[dump]]

===Usage===
* ''auf dem letzten Loch pfeifen'' - to be at the end of one's tether
* ''jemandem ein Loch in den Bauch fragen'' - to talk someone's head off

